Questions on mkdir , rmdir and rm command
------------------------------------------

1) What is the primary purpose of the mkdir command in Linux?

2) How would you create multiple directories at once using the mkdir command?

3) What is the difference between using mkdir dir1/dir2 and mkdir -p dir1/dir2?

4) What are the limitations of the rmdir command when deleting directories?

5) In what scenario would you use the rm command instead of rmdir to delete a directory?

6) What are the purposes of the -i and -v options in the rm command, and when might you use them?

